Kittu alias Krishnamurthy, was going back to his native place, after almost forty years. 
For Kittu, memories of his home town were circa 1980 the verdant countryside, the large artificial lake, the majestic temple by the lake and of course, street side cricket.

Madurantakam is a small town in Chengalpattu district, Tamil Nadu. 
The main temple and the lake were built during the Pallava and Chola periods respectively, several hundred years ago. 
It was home to the great Hindu saint and social reformer, Sri Ramanuja, the exponent of Vishistadvaitam, a famous branch of Hindu Philosophy.